      • runAfterEach

        Sub runAfterEach()
        Tests whether a AbstractBaliCustomBeforeAfter has been passed in and, if so, calls afterEach. Triggered from automatically all in-built assertions.
         
        Code Sample
        Dim globInt as Integer
        Class IntegerIncrementer as AbstractBaliCustomBeforeAfter
            Sub beforeEach()
                a = a + 1
            End Sub
            Sub afterEach()
                Print "Finished test"
            End Sub
        End Class
        Private Class CustomTester as AbstractBaliCustomTester
            Function runTests as Boolean
                Dim incrementer as New IntegerIncrementer()
                Call Me.testSuite.addCustomBeforeAfter(incrementer)
                Call Me.testSuite.checkStarted()
               
               Call Me.testSuite.runBeforeEach()   ' Increments a global variable
               Call Me.testSuite.describe("Test global variable").assertEqualsInteger(1, globInt)
               Call Me.testSuite.runAfterEach()
            End Function
        End Class

      • assertEqualsPrimitiveOrPrimitiveArray

        Function assertEqualsPrimitiveOrPrimitiveArray(expected As Variant, actual As Variant) As Boolean
        Tests two variant or variant arrays are the same.
        idx Argument Data Type Attributes Comments
        1 expected Variant Tests two variant or variant arrays are the same. 
        2 actual Variant Tests two variant or variant arrays are the same. 
         
        Code Sample
        Dim testSuite As New BaliTestSuite(|Variant Array Tests|)
        Dim a(7) As Variant, b() As Variant
        Dim i As integer
            
        For i = 0 To UBound(a)
            a(i) = i
        Next
            
        Call testSuite.describe(|Test array and not array|).assertEqualsPrimitiveOrPrimitiveArray(a, 1)   ' Returns false, expected is array, actual is not
            
        ReDim b(0)
        b(0) = 0
        Call testSuite.describe(|Test unequal array length|).assertEqualsPrimitiveOrPrimitiveArray(a, b)    ' Returns false, elements in arrays not equal
            
        ReDim b(i - 1)
        For i = 0 To UBound(b)
            b(i) = i
        Next
        Call testSuite.describe(|Test equal arrays|).assertEqualsPrimitiveOrPrimitiveArray(a, b)   ' Returns true
            
        b(0) = 1
        Call testSuite.describe(|Test first element different|).assertEqualsPrimitiveOrPrimitiveArray(a, b)   ' Returns false, element 1 not matching

      • assertNotEqualPrimitiveOrPrimitiveArray

        Function assertNotEqualPrimitiveOrPrimitiveArray(expected As Variant, actual As Variant) As Boolean
        Compares two variants or variant arrays and tests they are not the same, CStr-ing non-arrays
        idx Argument Data Type Attributes Comments
        1 expected Variant Compares two variants or variant arrays and tests they are not the same, CStr-ing non-arrays 
        2 actual Variant Compares two variants or variant arrays and tests they are not the same, CStr-ing non-arrays 
         
        Code Sample
        Dim testSuite as New BaliTestSuite("Test primitives")
        Dim actual as Integer
        actual = 2
        Call testSuite.describe("Test primitive").assertEqualsPrimitiveOrPrimitiveArray(3, actual)
        Call testSuite.describe("Test primitive data types").assertEqualsPrimitiveOrPrimitiveArray("2", actual)   ' Returns false, CStr(actual) matches "2"
